Dear users of LTUs,
new distribution of LTU software, supporting LTUvi (TTCvi not required more)
was released. It can be downloaded from:
http://epweb2.ph.bham.ac.uk/user/jusko/ltu/index.html


Client for LTU expert software:
------------------------------
- LTU_CLIENT_VERSION string constant in ltudim/ltuclient.c
  - left 2.8
         2.9    22.5.2012     -getCounters uses bakery
- preparing rpm distribution:
  trigger@pcalicebhm10: (x86_64):
  - match: 
    LTU_SW_VERSION in v/vme/ltu/ltu.h     4.1 04.05.2012   -not needed
    VERSION        in rpms/SPECS/ltuclient.spec
      (Release: 1   +1 for next rpm releases)
    VERSION        in v/bin/distrdimclient distrib
    Start vd/bin/distrdimclient distrib on pcalicebhm10 (x86_64 version)
       or                                  altri1       (i386)
   ->prepares ltuclient-VERSION.src.tar.gz in ~rpms/SOURCES
  cd rpms/SPECS ; rpmbuild -ba ltuclient.spec
   -> prepares ltuclient-VERSION.x86_64.rpm in ~rpms/RPMS
                                .i386

- installation:
  move: ~aj/rpms/RPMS/ltuclient-1.0-1.i386.rpm
  as root:
  rpm -e ltuclient ; rpm -q ltuclient
  rpm -ivh ltuclient-2.9-1.x86_64.rpm
  rpm -ivh ltuclient-1.0-2.i386.rpm
  as user:
  . /opt/ltuclient/scripts/setup.sh
       !!! instead vmecrate alias use ltuclient alias !!!
  ltuclient daq or
  $VMEBDIR/cratedim.sh daq
  $? is: 0:ok  4:parameter/environment error   8:server cannot be contacted

